Vice President Kamala Harris, in her role as Chair of the National Space Council, held a meeting with members of the Space Council's Users' Advisory Group (UAG) at the White House. During the meeting, the Vice President shared her vision for the UAG's work and expressed gratitude for their leadership and service. The UAG members discussed their perspectives and ideas regarding space and how the UAG can support the National Space Council. This meeting follows the inaugural UAG meeting under the current administration. The UAG's primary responsibility is to provide recommendations to the National Space Council on various space-related policies and strategies, including those related to government policies, laws, regulations, treaties, international instruments, and space programs across civil, commercial, and national security sectors.